-need to make a package.json; manifest file. metadata about the node app.
-put client side code in public code.
-server.js is the backend of our application. it contains the routes and stuff.
-procfile tells heroku what commands to use.

-set up heroku account. login to it on web to remember pass.
-install heroku cli tools. login to heroku from command line

-check if your app can run locally with heroku. "heroku local web"; heroku automatically puts your code on localhost:5000/

-http server -> same kinda deal as "heroku local web"
-heroku create -> to create app.
-heroku logs --tail --app peaceful-caverns-43698 -> to see logs
-heroku apps -> see apps.
